### Run Freebayes on all Tms
Because when I run all samples freebayes get really slow, I will try to use parallel

1) Install Freebayes

```
git clone --recursive git://github.com/ekg/freebayes.git
make
```




# Use screen


```
$ screen -S freebayes_Tms
$ srun -p axiom --nodes 1 --ntasks=36 --mem=150GB --time 10-00:00:0 --account=tschwand_default --pty bash
module add Bioinformatics/Software/vital-it
freebayes freebayes-parallel


freebayes-parallel <(fasta_generate_regions.py 3_Tms_b3v08.fasta 100000) 36 -f 3_Tms_b3v08.fasta --bam-list inds_all --min-mapping-quality 30 --min-coverage 5 > Tms_all_new.vcf

```



freebayes -f 3_Tms_b3v08.fasta --bam-list inds_all --min-mapping-quality 30 --min-coverage 5 > Tms_all_new.vcf
